[243x538]Introduction
[107x517]The Lorenz system was introduced in \[30\] as a simplified model for atmospheric
[78x503]convection. Numerical simulations have shown that the Lorenz system admits a
[78x489]strange attractor, called the Lorenz attractor, which became one of the most iconic
[78x475]examples in the field.
[90x461]A rigorous mathematical approach was developed with the introduction of the so
[78x447]called geometric Lorenz flow by \[1, 26\], which mimicks simulation of the dynamics of
[78x434]the Lorenz flow, and which has a robust strange attractor under
