[78x420]Later in \[37, 38\] it was shown that the actual Lorenz attractor is indeed a singular
[78x406]hyperbolic attractor, further showing that the geometric Lorenz attractor represents
[78x392]the Lorenz attractor well. Moreover, it admits the so called Sinai-Ruelle-Bowen
[78x378](SRB) measure, which is ergodic \[11\]. Its statistical properties, such as mixing
[78x364]rates, limit theorems and their stability under various perturbations, were studied
[78x350]intensively (see for example, \[31, 10, 9, 7, 14, 13, 24\]).
[90x336]Another class of systems with similar properties was introduced in \[35\] called the
