[197x322]. A fundamental difference between these is that the attrac-
[78x308]tor of the system introduced by Rovella is not robust under perturbations, but still
[78x294]abundant in a measure theoretic sense. The set of measures for which the system
[78x280]is chaotic is called Rovella parameters and satisfies strong chaotic properties \[8\];
[78x266]moreover, restricted to this set the system is stochastically stable \[32, 33\]. In \[34\]
[78x252]the authors addressed thermodynamic formalism for it. Up to now, the contracting
[78x238]Lorenz flow and one dimensional maps with critical points remain a profound exam-
[78x224]ple of a truly nonuniformly hyperbolic systems, which is studied via construction of
[78x210]induced schemes. We refer to \[3\] for a comprehensive account of these constructions.
